bug.short_desc: Erasure of method signature should not include type parameters

long_desc.thetext:
Add three error messages, one for each method: Erasure of method foo(List x) is the same as another method.
(In reply to comment #3) > Consider the following example: > > 1. import java.util.List; > 2. > 3. class X { > 4. void foo(List<Integer> x) {} > 5. void foo(List<String> x) {} > 6. void foo(List<Double> x) {} > 7. } > > Line6: Method foo(List<Double>) has the same erasure foo(List<E>) as another > method in type X > > Line4: Method foo(List<Integer>) has the same erasure foo(List<E>) as > another method in type X > > Line5: Method foo(List<String>) has the same erasure foo(List<E>) as another > method in type X > > Q. Should we put up three errors or only two. Should there be any errors for > void foo(List<Integer> x) {} (the first function). > > Thanks
